    summary: "Treasury market depth has recovered to its best level since 2021 after the brief April 2025 tariff shock, while the SEC's central-clearing mandate now phases in over Dec 2026 (cash) and June 2027 (repo), with FICC and a new CME clearing entity competing to absorb the flow.",
